{"title":"LogicInsight - Nutanix Cluster Physical Disk Overview","description":"### **📊 LogicInsight - Nutanix Cluster Physical Disk Overview Dashboard Explanation**\n\nThis **LogicInsight - Nutanix Cluster Physical Disk Overview** dashboard provides a **detailed view of the physical disks across the Nutanix cluster**, helping administrators monitor disk health, status, capacity, and utilization. Below is a section-by-section breakdown of the dashboard:\n\n***\n\n## **1️⃣ Total Disks & Status (Blue Section - Top)**\n\nThis section provides a **quick overview of disk availability and health**:\n\n-   **Total Bad Disks (Green Box):**\n\n    -   Indicates the number of disks that have failed or are malfunctioning.\n    -   A value of **0** means all disks are healthy.\n\n-   **Total Disks:**\n\n    -   The total number of disks present in the cluster.\n\n-   **Online Disks:**\n\n    -   The number of disks that are currently active and functional.\n\n-   **Disks Mounted:**\n\n    -   The number of disks successfully mounted and available for use.\n\n✔ **Why It’s Important?**\\\nThis section helps administrators **quickly detect and troubleshoot storage issues** by identifying failed disks and ensuring all necessary disks are online and mounted.\n\n***\n\n## **2️⃣ Disk Types & Capacity (Yellow Section - Middle Left)**\n\n-   **Disk Types Pie Chart:**\n\n    -   Shows the percentage of **HDDs (Hard Disk Drives)** and **SSDs (Solid-State Drives)** in the cluster.\n    -   **HDD (Hard Disk Drive):** Traditional mechanical storage, used for bulk storage.\n    -   **SSD (Solid-State Drive):** Faster storage with better performance for high-speed workloads.\n\n-   **Host Storage Capacity Table:**\n\n    -   Displays the total **disk capacity, disk usage, and free disk space per host**.\n    -   Helps in monitoring **which hosts have enough storage available** and which are running low.\n\n✔ **Why It’s Important?**\\\nUnderstanding the **distribution of SSD vs. HDD** helps in performance tuning, while tracking storage usage ensures **efficient storage management and capacity planning**.\n\n***\n\n## **3️⃣ Cluster & Hosts Disks Summary (Right Section)**\n\n-   **Cluster Disks Table:**\n\n    -   Provides detailed information about each individual disk, including:\n\n        -   **Cluster Name & Host Name** – Identifies where each disk is located.\n        -   **Disk ID & Serial Number** – Unique identifiers for each disk.\n        -   **Storage Tier (HDD/SSD)** – Indicates the type of storage.\n        -   **Mount Path** – Shows where the disk is mounted in the system.\n        -   **Disk Status (Online, Mounted, Bad, Size, etc.)** – Highlights whether the disk is operational or has any issues.\n\n✔ **Why It’s Important?**\\\nThis table helps in **identifying faulty disks, tracking their physical locations, and ensuring storage health**.\n\n***\n\n## **4️⃣ Host Disk Capacity (Bottom Right Table)**\n\n-   **Lists each disk per host with detailed storage usage data**, including:\n\n    -   **Disk Capacity** – Total storage capacity of the disk.\n    -   **Disk Usage** – How much space is being used.\n    -   **Disk Free** – Available free space.\n\n✔ **Why It’s Important?**\\\nBy monitoring **disk usage trends**, administrators can **proactively manage storage expansions or rebalancing**.\n\n***\n\n### **📌 Why This Dashboard Matters?**\n\n-   **🔍 Fast Issue Detection** – Quickly **detect and replace faulty disks** to prevent failures.\n-   **📊 Capacity Planning** – Ensure **storage is distributed efficiently** and plan for future needs.\n-   **⚡ Performance Optimization** – Understand the balance of SSD vs. HDD usage for **better system performance**.\n-   **✅ Health Monitoring** – Keep track of **disk mounting status, storage utilization, and disk failures**.","widgets":[{"id":739967362197144,"definition":{"type":"image","url":"https://logicappupdate.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/dash_logo.png","sizing":"cover","has_background":true,"has_bord